text:
Yeah... the form is customizable. You can create an upto 3 column layout with the dnd form editor. Also if you modify the embed like this:

default embed:
```&lt;script charset="utf-8" type="text/javascript" src="//js-eu1.hsforms.net/forms/embed/v2.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
&lt;script&gt;
  hbspt.forms.create({
    region: "eu1",
    portalId: "XXXXXXXXX",
    formId: "XXXXXX-XXXXXXX-XXXXXXX"
  });
&lt;/script&gt;```
changed embed:
```&lt;script charset="utf-8" type="text/javascript" src="//js-eu1.hsforms.net/forms/embed/v2.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
&lt;script&gt;
  hbspt.forms.create({
    region: "eu1",
    portalId: "XXXXXXXXX",
    formId: "XXXXXX-XXXXXXX-XXXXXXX",
    css: ''
  });
&lt;/script&gt;```
(adding the `css: ''` part)

The form won't load the default HS styling and therefore can be styled through the CSS of the system you're embedding it in
